		<main>
			<h1>Cherry Cream Cheese Dessert</h1>
			<p>Melts in your mouth!</p>
			<p>Makes 8 servings</p>
			<img src="../imgs/cherrycream.jpg" height="250">

			<div class="servings">
				<h3>Servings</h3>
				<button id="dec">-</button>
				<span id="serving-count">8</span>
				<button id="inc">+</button>
			</div>

			<h2>Ingredients</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<span class="count" base="0.09375">0.75</span> cup graham cracker crumbs (about <span class="count" base="1.5">12</span> squares)
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="count" base="0.25">2</span> tbsp sugar
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="count" base="0.25">2</span> tbsp butter, melted
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="count" base="0.125">1</span> can (<span class="count" base="1.75">14</span> oz) sweetened condensed milk
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="count" base="0.03125">0.25</span> cup lemon juice
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="count" base="0.125">1</span> tsp vanilla extract
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="count" base="0.125">1</span> can (<span class="count" base="2.625">21</span> oz) cherry pie filling
				</li>
				<li>
					<span class="count" base="0.125">1</span> package (<span class="count" base="1">8</span> oz) cream cheese, softened
				</li>
			</ul>
			<h2>Instructions</h2>
			<ol>
				<li>
					In a small bowl, combine the cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Divide among 8 dessert dishes, about 4 rounded teaspoonfuls in each.
				</li>
				<li>
					In a small bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually add milk until blended. Beat in lemon juice and vanilla. Spoon 1/4 cup into each dish. Top with pie filling, about 1/4 cup in each.
				</li>
			</ol>
			<h2>Nutrition Facts</h2>
			<p><b>1 serving: 418 calories</b></p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					18g fat (11g saturated fat)
				</li>
				<li>
					56mg cholesterol
				</li>
				<li>
					228mg sodium
				</li>
				<li>
					59g carbohydrate (51g sugars, 1g fiber)
				</li>
				<li>
					7g protein
				</li>
			</ul>
		</main>
